      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "**Key functional groups / motifs**\n- **Aromatic rings (2 total):**\n  - One **phenyl ring** on the right (lipophilic, hydrophobic anchor).\n  - One **catechol-like ring** (benzene with **two phenolic OH** groups) on the left (polar H-bonding, can chelate/oxidize).\n- **Amide:** `C(=O)N...` = **secondary amide** (N\u2013H present, but **not basic**; amide N is resonance-stabilized).\n- **Conjugated alkene (\u03b1,\u03b2-unsaturated system):** `N#C/C(=C\\Ar)C(=O)N...` (a **Michael acceptor-like** conjugation, though less reactive due to strong EWG pattern and aryl substitution).\n- **Nitrile:** `N#C` (polar, H-bond acceptor, not protonatable).\n- **Two H-bond donors:** phenolic OH (2) + amide NH (1) = **3 donors** total.\n- **No tertiary amine / no protonatable basic nitrogen.**",
