      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "**Structural alerts relevant to CYP2D6 inhibition**\n- Typical CYP2D6 inhibitors often have a **protonatable basic N** (e.g., tertiary amine) + aromatic hydrophobes. This molecule **lacks** that hallmark feature.\n- Contains **multiple phenols (catechol)**: can increase polarity and reduce membrane partitioning; also can be rapidly conjugated (phase II), often reducing time at enzyme site.",
