    {
      "step_id": "0420d21a",
      "step_index": 4,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 2) REASON about structure\u2013CYP2D6 inhibition SAR (WHY features matter)\n**CYP2D6 binding/inhibition drivers (common SAR):**\n- A **basic, protonated nitrogen** forms a key ionic interaction with **Asp301** in CYP2D6\u2019s active site (a major determinant for many competitive inhibitors/substrates).\n- **Aromatic/lipophilic regions** occupy hydrophobic pockets and help position the basic N correctly.",
      "tool_name": null,
