      "step_index": 5,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "**This molecule:**\n- Has **aromatic/lipophilic rings** (favorable for binding in general).\n- But the only nitrogens are **amide N (non-basic)** and **nitrile N (non-basic)** \u2192 at physiological pH, **no cationic center** to engage Asp301.\n- The **catechol** and **amide** add H-bonding and polarity, which can:\n  - Reduce passive diffusion into the microsomal membrane environment where CYPs reside.\n  - Favor alternative binding modes that are **weaker** for CYP2D6 (which tends to prefer cationic ligands).",
      "tool_name": null,
